nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Serine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets serine through chemically explicit, convergent routes centered on three plausible immediate precursors: glycine, formaldehyde, and glycolaldehyde/glyceraldehyde-derived C3 oxygenates. The core endpoint chemistry is made explicit through two prebiotically discussed motifs: (i) hydroxymethylation of glycine by formaldehyde to give serine, and (ii) Strecker-type formation of a serine nitrile/aminonitrile precursor from glycolaldehyde-derived aldehydes followed by hydrolysis. Hydrothermal environments generate reduced C1/C2/C3 feedstocks such as formate, acetate, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, and pyruvate on Fe-S and oxide minerals; surface environments convert these into HCN-derived aminonitriles, sugars, and glyceraldehyde under wet-dry, UV, and evaporitic conditions; biochemical/prebiotic settings then hydrolyze, transaminate, and condense these pools into serine. Ten pathways are enumerated by combining distinct upstream routes into the same explicit endpoint chemistry.\n\nMOLECULES (17 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H4N2 (glycine nitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C3H6O4 (glyceric acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H5NO (serine nitrile/serine aminonitrile precursor) [hub_